		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> July 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I had <sic>intendid</sic> to have written<lb/> you long ago &#38; acknowledged the receipt of<lb/> the prayer Books which I was much pleased with<lb/> I <sic>allso</sic> received a Bible from <persName>Mr Hart</persName>.  I did<lb/> not know that I was a subscriber to the same as<lb/> I had a very fine one but as it came I have<lb/> received it.  I owe you an apology for not sending<lb/> the money for them&#44; but as I have had some<lb/> very heavy payments to make not alone in my<lb/> Business but privately I have postponed doing so<lb/> but will in a short time remit you a check for<lb/> the amount &#38; hope the delay will not incommode<lb/> you.  I am generally in my affairs very punctual but<lb/> as I said above I have had very much to pay of<lb/> late for others accommodation&#44; I can not<lb/> close my letter without congratulating you on<lb/> entire success you have gained over the Gentleman<lb/> they term here <persName>Dr Mayer</persName> I like yourself am<lb/> anxious to know by what authority &#38; from whose<lb/> hands he claims the title of Revd Dr.  It is easily<lb/> found out&#44; his followers here wish to give him<lb/> position &#38; have therefore Dubbed him Dr. but it<lb/> will not answer.  <persName>Mr. <hi rend="underline">Poser</hi></persName> is bad enough in<lb/> his ideas of reform &#38; this man is quite his</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>equal not being able to keep my religion as I<lb/> properly should it might be said I have no<lb/> right to find fault&#44; but bad as I may be in<lb/> not following the precepts as laid down I am &#38;<lb/> have <sic>allways</sic> been an anti reformist in any<lb/> shape &#38; will never give my consent to any change<lb/> no matter how small.  I feel that to change<lb/> any one portion of our forms destroys the whole&#44;<lb/> &#38; the more I read your <sic>excellant</sic> Book the<lb/> stronger my conviction&#44; but enough I am not<lb/> qualified to write on this grave subject in<lb/> a short time you shall hear from wishing<lb/> you health &#38; happiness I Remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">M. N. Nathan</persName></p>
		</body>
